## Wiki maintenance

The company knowledge wiki lives at `context/wiki/`. It is the synthesized knowledge layer for all [project] operations.

**Rules for all agents:**

1. **Read the wiki first.** Before searching scattered files, check the relevant wiki page.
2. **Update on change.** When new information arrives, update the relevant wiki page.
3. **Log every change.** Append an entry to `context/wiki/log.md`. Format: `## [YYYY-MM-DD] action | description`
4. **Update the index.** When a page is added, renamed, or removed, update `context/wiki/index.md`.
5. **Cross-reference.** When updating one page, check if related pages also need updating.
6. **Date all metrics.** Every number that can go stale must include the date it was recorded.
7. **Synthesize, don't duplicate.** Wiki pages are concise summaries. Link to source files for full detail.
8. **Under 300 lines per page.** If a page grows beyond this, split it.

